Separating racial categories

Educational attainment by race

“Is there disproportionate education attainment by race in the county?”

For ACS datasets on educational attainment is “population 25 years or older” White populations have a much higher proportion of the total and the other educational attainment categories, followed by Asian populations. The lowest educational attainment in all the categories were American Indian, Black / African American, Native Hawaiian and other Pacific Islander as well Bi- and Multi-Racial Populations. These findings highlight equity issues in education and educational attainment for different racial categories
